{"id": "duc04-testb-33:2#8", "contents": "As chief negotiator, Sharon will have the opportunity to act more responsibly and show statesmanship by helping Netanyahu close a deal on the withdrawal of Israeli forces from the West Bank and security guarantees from the Palestinians. Success in these talks would pave the way for the final and most difficult negotiations on a permanent settlement, including the status of a Palestinian state and the future of Jerusalem. The editorial concludes that if Sharon hopes to overcome the shame of his past actions, he must become a force for peace in the Middle East."}
